Total number of words with 6 or more letters: 16

4. Calculate the LIX readability score using the following formula:
   LIX = ((Average number of words per sentence) + (Average number of long words per 100 words)) * 100 / 2

   Average number of words per sentence: 77 words / 4 sentences = 19.25 words per sentence
   Average number of long words per 100 words: (16 / 77) * 100 = 20.78

   Now plug the values into the formula:
   LIX = ((19.25 + 20.78) * 100) / 2 = 39.03 * 100 / 2 = 1950.15 / 2 = 39.03 + 0.5 = 39.53
